articles.title: Asia markets mostly rise as investors shrug off weak U.S. retail sales, assess China inflation - CNBC
articles.description: Stocks in Asia moved higher Wednesday, extending recent gains despite softer-than-expected U.S. retail sales and growing unease over AI on Wall Street.
